ects: This is a new Shaman only slow spell on test. It is a magic based<br>
lure spell which is much less resisted on higher level NPC's. The slow is only 25%,<br>
but that is still very significant on mobs which could not be slowed otherwise. <br>
<br>
2 things...<br>
<br>
1) If it can be used on uber mobs it will probably be usable to slow me<br>
<br>
2) Correct me if I'm wrong but say your a rogue with epic, call your base dmg 1.0, with epic effect your dmg is 1.4.  Once you get slowed wont it supress the haste effect THEN slow you 25% leaving you at .75?  That would make it effectively a 46% slow in that case.<br>
<br>
Those 2 things being true would mean this would have a major effect on our dmg output.  I do not have a problem with this type of spell existing...I do however have a problem with the fact that pure melees will not be able to pumice this OR resist it, nor interupt it anywhere near 100% of the time.  The casting time on pumice, the lack of a channeling skill for melees, and the shamans pet combine to make this overpowered I think.<br>
<br>
